1
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:21,967
Tiffany?

2
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:27,300
Celeste, are you
expecting a visitor?

3
00:00:27,367 --> 00:00:28,367
Nothing.

4
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:30,167
Did you see the young girl?

5
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:32,300
She looked like Tiffany.

6
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:34,733
- Who?
- Actually nothing.

7
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:35,967
Forget about it.

8
00:00:36,033 --> 00:00:36,967
My eyes are just playing tricks
on me.

9
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:38,800
So how are the two of you?

10
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:41,133
Your history is not a secret.

11
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,433
Actually, it's a bit
awkward at first

12
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:47,100
but as time goes by
we became okay.

13
00:00:47,167 --> 00:00:49,000
Well, I hope I get
to know her better.

14
00:00:49,067 --> 00:00:51,733
You will like Celeste
once you get to know her.

15
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:56,633
I think Hazel will be here
more often

16
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,700
because of her proposal.

17
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,900
You know what?
I changed my mind.

18
00:01:00,967 --> 00:01:05,900
Can we just cancel Hazel's
offer and all of that?

19
00:01:05,967 --> 00:01:08,333
I guess there's nothing
I should be worried about them.

20
00:01:08,433 --> 00:01:10,033
Past is past.

21
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:12,433
We have completely forgotten
everything

22
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:15,300
that we've gone through,
all resentments.

23
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:18,000
She's happy. And I'm happy
that she's happy.

24
00:01:18,067 --> 00:01:21,400
Did you tell Celeste about
your dinner date with Aurelia?

25
00:01:21,467 --> 00:01:23,667
I was supposed to tell her...

26
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:26,333
but she sounded so stressed
in Sorsogon.

27
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:28,167
I don't want to add
to her worries.

28
00:01:28,233 --> 00:01:29,500
I'm just warning you.

29
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:31,367
This could blow up on your face.

30
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:33,933
What could possibly go wrong
with one dinner?

31
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,467
It's not that
I have doubts.

32
00:01:36,533 --> 00:01:40,567
But my point is,
her intention is doubtful.

33
00:01:40,667 --> 00:01:44,967
And she's doing that just
to make sure

34
00:01:45,033 --> 00:01:51,300
there's no chance for Mikoy
to fall in love.

35
00:01:51,367 --> 00:01:56,633
As they say,
keep your friends close,

36
00:01:56,700 --> 00:02:03,633
your enemies closer, and
your rival in love the closest.

37
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:10,600
So when the chance comes
you can easily crush the enemy.

38
00:02:10,667 --> 00:02:15,733
I knew it. Just one look at that
woman I know I can't trust her.

39
00:02:15,833 --> 00:02:20,367
I can see right through here
and I know she's not sincere.

40
00:02:20,433 --> 00:02:21,433
What will you do?

41
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:24,800
I won't let her
ruin my plans.

42
00:02:24,867 --> 00:02:29,067
I will show her that
Mikoy is just mine.

43
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:31,967
And if she ever makes a move
on Mikoy

44
00:02:32,033 --> 00:02:34,467
I swear I will tear her down.

45
00:02:34,533 --> 00:02:36,467
Are the people here like this?

46
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:37,867
I prepared for this
presentation

47
00:02:37,933 --> 00:02:39,067
but they didn't show up.

48
00:02:39,133 --> 00:02:41,900
Tiff, you just have
to be patient with them.

49
00:02:41,967 --> 00:02:44,100
I waited there
the whole day.

50
00:02:44,167 --> 00:02:47,067
My eyes already turned white but
not even one of them showed up.

51
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,600
Tiffany, if that is
your attitude

52
00:02:48,667 --> 00:02:51,333
then it's justified if no one
came here.

53
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,633
You think you are the center
of the Universe.

54
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:55,400
Who are you?

55
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:57,333
You think so highly of yourself.

56
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,833
Take back what you said.

57
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:00,233
Why should I take it back?

58
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:03,167
That's the truth.

59
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,400
Tiffany, wait.

60
00:03:04,467 --> 00:03:05,700
Let go of me!

61
00:03:05,767 --> 00:03:07,233
Who are you to insult me?

62
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:09,033
Insult you?

63
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:12,033
Is that what you think
if people criticize you?

64
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:13,733
People who tell you the truth?

65
00:03:15,933 --> 00:03:17,633
Tiffany, look...

66
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:19,400
I'm just trying
to help you.

67
00:03:19,467 --> 00:03:22,400
And just because you're good,
you're smart.

68
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,933
It doesn't mean that you can
judge other people.

69
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,400
Have you thought
about why no one came?

70
00:03:27,467 --> 00:03:30,567
That maybe they are busy fishing
or working

71
00:03:30,633 --> 00:03:32,567
because if they will attend
to your meeting

72
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:35,000
how will they feed
their families?

73
00:03:35,067 --> 00:03:36,500
Their children?

74
00:03:36,567 --> 00:03:38,067
Tiffany, tell me.

75
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:41,433
Tiffany, look...

76
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:45,767
in this situation it's you
who is judgmental.

77
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:48,767
At the very least
you should open your mind

78
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:50,867
to other people's lives.

79
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:56,733
If you can't open your mind,
if you can't open your heart,

80
00:03:56,833 --> 00:04:02,433
if your heart is closed
you will live alone forever.

81
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:06,133
And you will keep on blaming
others for your failures.

82
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:12,167
But the truth is
you should blame yourself.

83
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:21,233
Oh my, have patience
with May-May.

84
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:24,200
Sometimes she talks too much.

85
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,133
That's okay, Grandma.
I'm used to it.

86
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:32,967
That's why I'm not affected
with May-May.

87
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:34,433
You can't sleep?

88
00:05:38,633 --> 00:05:40,233
I think it's a full moon.

89
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:41,733
My mind is wide awake.

90
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,100
You even blame the moon.

91
00:05:43,167 --> 00:05:46,500
You don't want to admit that
something is bothering you.

92
00:05:46,567 --> 00:05:49,967
Just a reminder your beautiful
grandma is here.

93
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:53,333
You can share anything,
everything, whatever.

94
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,500
I know that.

95
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:58,000
I know that you're always
on my side to support me.

96
00:05:59,933 --> 00:06:02,833
Do you remember
when you were a child?

97
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:04,600
When you can't sleep

98
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:08,833
I always tell
your favorite story.

99
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:11,233
The rabbit and the turtle.

100
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:13,200
That's it.

101
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:16,300
Spoiler alert the turtle wins.

102
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:18,200
I don't know.

103
00:06:18,267 --> 00:06:21,167
Was it really the turtle
who won?

104
00:06:21,233 --> 00:06:24,867
Of course. He was the one who
reached the finish line, right?

105
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:26,300
He came in first.

106
00:06:27,967 --> 00:06:30,867
I don't know. I think
it's the rabbit

107
00:06:30,933 --> 00:06:35,200
who is the winner in the story.

108
00:06:35,267 --> 00:06:38,800
If you think about it...

109
00:06:38,867 --> 00:06:43,267
everyone expected him to win
but he didn't.

110
00:06:43,367 --> 00:06:44,933
He did what he wanted.

111
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,667
He followed
what his heart wants.

112
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:50,567
But he's lazy, right?

113
00:06:50,633 --> 00:06:53,233
It seems he didn't go there
to race, right?

114
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:55,333
Oh my...

115
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:58,567
I think that is the problem
with the world, Grandson.

116
00:06:58,633 --> 00:07:00,633
Everybody is racing.

117
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:04,400
Everybody wants to reach
the finish line.

118
00:07:04,467 --> 00:07:08,133
You know sometimes
we are like a turtle.

119
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:10,600
We're carrying heavy
burden in our hearts,

120
00:07:10,667 --> 00:07:13,433
we want to finish the story
right away.

121
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:16,500
We want to reach the finish line
right away.

122
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,567
Hoping that maybe what's waiting
for us there

123
00:07:18,633 --> 00:07:23,867
is more beautiful, happier.

124
00:07:23,933 --> 00:07:28,733
But for me, it's better
to be a rabbit.

125
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:32,133
You will just sit under a tree.

126
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:35,767
Close your eyes and blink.

127
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:39,600
You will dream,
you will aspire.

128
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:05,333
Sometimes life's expectation
of us is too heavy.

129
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:12,100
What hurts is we feel that
we can carry that alone.

130
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:16,400
We refuse to accept
help from others.

131
00:08:16,467 --> 00:08:18,833
Even if it's very hard for us

132
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:23,067
and our burdens are too heavy
for us to carry.

133
00:08:23,167 --> 00:08:29,333
We don't want to stop and
breathe first even for a moment.

134
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:36,000
Because we believe that
we can do everything alone.

135
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:49,867
But that's the scariest part
when we start to believe

136
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:52,433
that we can do everything.

137
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:57,533
We learn to keep
resentments in our hearts...

138
00:08:58,633 --> 00:09:03,967
and when it piles up, the more
it makes our burden heavier.

139
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:21,567
All of us have
our shortcomings.

140
00:09:22,867 --> 00:09:27,700
All of us are carrying a burden.

141
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:31,100
All of us have doubts.

142
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:52,200
All of us have regrets.

143
00:09:52,267 --> 00:09:56,100
Decisions that
we go back to.

144
00:09:56,167 --> 00:10:00,533
All of us did something wrong
that we want to correct.

145
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:11,367
So the best thing that we have
to learn is to stop racing.

146
00:10:11,433 --> 00:10:19,400
And sometimes we have to breathe
and rest our tired hearts.

147
00:10:19,467 --> 00:10:23,433
And open ourselves again
to the possibilities

148
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:27,900
that what we are looking
for in our lives, the things

149
00:10:27,967 --> 00:10:32,867
that will make us happy
are just around us,

150
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:36,900
and in the people beside us.

151
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:41,800
That whatever our burdens
are it will be lighter

152
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:46,500
if we are with the people
who love us.

153
00:10:46,567 --> 00:10:50,567
It's like I want to be
a rabbit in your story, Grandma.

154
00:10:50,633 --> 00:10:53,567
What's with you? It's my dream
to be a ninja turtle.

155
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:56,567
You are full of nonsense.

156
00:10:56,633 --> 00:10:57,767
What's with you?

157
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:59,433
It would be better
if you go to sleep.

158
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:03,133
You rest and have
a beautiful dream.

159
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,900
What do you want to dream

160
00:11:05,967 --> 00:11:10,633
or who do you want
to dream about?

161
00:11:10,733 --> 00:11:12,133
Ouch.

162
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:18,167
This old woman.

163
00:11:18,233 --> 00:11:20,133
You're really something.

164
00:11:41,567 --> 00:11:44,067
What you are cooking
seems delicious.

165
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:47,167
Of course, I included
my secret ingredient.

166
00:11:47,233 --> 00:11:49,500
It's an everlasting love.

167
00:12:00,633 --> 00:12:02,633
Celeste.

168
00:12:14,667 --> 00:12:17,667
What are you doing here?

169
00:12:17,733 --> 00:12:19,300
You did something to me?

170
00:12:19,367 --> 00:12:21,167
Hey, I didn't do anything.

171
00:12:21,233 --> 00:12:22,767
You're not my type.

172
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,167
Grandma Ikay just asked me
to come here to wake you up

173
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:27,700
because you will deliver food.

174
00:12:27,767 --> 00:12:30,267
Tell Grandma that I will be out
in a while.

175
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:33,533
Wow, you woke up late.

176
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,700
It looks like you
have a good sleep.

177
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:37,167
Did you have a nice dream?

178
00:12:37,233 --> 00:12:39,900
Did you reach heaven?

179
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:41,533
You talk too much.

180
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:43,800
Get out. I'll get myself ready.

181
00:12:43,867 --> 00:12:47,167
Oh my, you're so sensitive
and defensive.

182
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:51,200
That's because you're dreaming
about my cousin Celeste.

183
00:12:52,367 --> 00:12:54,233
Of course not.

184
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:57,300
Come on, you're denying it
when I heard it.

185
00:12:57,367 --> 00:12:59,267
You're whispering her name.

186
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:01,300
Mikoy, that's serious.

187
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:03,900
If you keep on suppressing
what you truly feel.

188
00:13:03,967 --> 00:13:05,833
It might come out of your chest.

189
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:07,133
It's up to you.

190
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:10,100
It might swell and burst and
become ruptured appendicitis.

191
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:12,367
That's dangerous, Mikoy.

192
00:13:14,133 --> 00:13:15,533
You should brush your teeth.

193
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:17,433
It's like you're the one
who just woke up.

194
00:13:24,767 --> 00:13:27,200
He's right.
I put on lipstick first.

195
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,067
- Celeste, come on.
- It's okay.

196
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:03,533
Hazel!

197
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,500
Good morning.

198
00:14:08,567 --> 00:14:09,867
Good morning.

199
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:11,900
- Good morning.
- Hello.

200
00:14:11,967 --> 00:14:13,233
So...

201
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:16,433
Welcome partners and
welcome to the future.

202
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:19,733
- Wow, where will we sit?
- Thank you.

203
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:20,933
Let's go here.

204
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:24,400
She looks like a dog.

205
00:14:28,567 --> 00:14:32,667
So are you ready to find out
how our beloved pili nuts

206
00:14:32,733 --> 00:14:34,367
will take the world by storm?

207
00:14:34,433 --> 00:14:35,833
- Yes!
- We're ready.

208
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:38,300
Great. Let's begin.

209
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:50,167
Basti, please answer my call.

210
00:14:54,467 --> 00:14:58,133
Hey Tiff, is it me
you're calling?

211
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,467
Hello?

212
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:02,000
Basti?

213
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:03,833
Basti, I'm really sorry.

214
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:05,167
I'm really, really sorry.

215
00:15:05,233 --> 00:15:06,167
I'm really sorry
for what happened.

216
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:07,900
I'm really sorry.

217
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:11,567
Hey, that's okay. All right.

218
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:16,567
I didn't expect
that you can apologize.

219
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:19,033
I hate you.

220
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:22,000
Don't push it okay?

221
00:15:22,067 --> 00:15:25,067
Okay, fine.

222
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:26,533
Apology accepted.

223
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,400
Thank you, Basti.

224
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:35,400
Okay so let's begin.

225
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:37,267
- Yes.
- Okay.

226
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:41,667
So first, the general perception
of the international market

227
00:15:41,733 --> 00:15:44,800
is that Himalayan salt
is a good type of salt.

228
00:15:44,867 --> 00:15:47,633
Many believe in
its healing powers.

229
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:52,400
Hence, we saw the explosion
of Himalayan products.

230
00:15:52,467 --> 00:15:56,667
That's why I thought
why don't we fuse the idea

231
00:15:56,733 --> 00:15:59,233
of healing into our pili nuts?

232
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:04,200
Therefore...

233
00:16:05,233 --> 00:16:09,100
I present to you Himalayan
salted pili nuts.

234
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:11,833
Healing has never
been this delicious.

235
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:14,733
That's good.

236
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:16,533
That's beautiful.

237
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:21,100
That product is saleable.

238
00:16:21,167 --> 00:16:24,433
On a sad note, I don't think
it's a good idea.

239
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:25,633
Because salt is salt.

240
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:28,200
And there's a huge percentage
of the consumer market

241
00:16:28,267 --> 00:16:31,033
that is fully aware
of the dangers

242
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:33,200
of consuming excess salt.

243
00:16:33,267 --> 00:16:36,000
It doesn't sit well with me.

244
00:16:36,067 --> 00:16:40,300
We're going to lose a huge chunk
of health-conscious consumers.

245
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:43,733
And people might think
that the pili nut

246
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:45,500
is delicious because salt
was put into it.

247
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:49,133
Plus fact that we alienating
a huge percent of the actual

248
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:51,200
growing market of consumers
that have grown

249
00:16:51,267 --> 00:16:54,033
to be very environmentally
conscious

250
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:55,433
about their food intake.

251
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:58,967
I mean if you did your research
which I'm sure you did...

252
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:01,867
or you didn't.

253
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:07,867
Basically, they find
Himalayan salt dangerous

254
00:17:07,933 --> 00:17:08,867
to the environment.

255
00:17:08,933 --> 00:17:12,267
So I don't think
it's a good idea

256
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:15,800
because it is something that
we're going to say

257
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:17,400
that pili nut
is not sustainable.

258
00:17:17,467 --> 00:17:19,400
It has a great effect
on the environment.

259
00:17:19,467 --> 00:17:22,233
So it was a maybe
in the beginning

260
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:26,167
but it's a no for me.

261
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:28,433
Yes, too much salt is bad.

262
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:30,300
You have a point there, Celeste.

263
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:34,500
Okay, moving on.

264
00:17:34,567 --> 00:17:35,533
Yeah.

265
00:17:37,733 --> 00:17:38,967
Ice cream,

266
00:17:39,033 --> 00:17:42,333
if there's one product that
really stood the test of time

267
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:44,467
regardless of the situation.

268
00:17:44,533 --> 00:17:47,267
Whether there is a pandemic
or not, boom or bust,

269
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:51,067
ice cream consistently posted
growth in our global sales.

270
00:17:51,167 --> 00:17:54,233
So I've thought,
what if we partner

271
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:56,833
with an established
ice cream company.

272
00:17:56,900 --> 00:18:01,367
And create our own ice cream
flavored with our pili nuts.

273
00:18:01,433 --> 00:18:04,200
Hence every scoop will make you
go nuts

274
00:18:04,267 --> 00:18:08,067
with our Sorsogon pili flavored
ice cream.

275
00:18:08,133 --> 00:18:10,400
But I know that Celeste

276
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:13,000
is very concerned
about our healthy eaters.

277
00:18:13,067 --> 00:18:16,567
But let's admit that every once
in a while

278
00:18:16,633 --> 00:18:19,633
don't you think we should allow
ourselves to indulge

279
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:22,033
in at least a scoop
of ice cream?

280
00:18:22,933 --> 00:18:23,933
Right, Celeste?

281
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:29,067
Your idea is fun, Hazel.

282
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:30,800
- It's delicious.
- Yes.

283
00:18:32,667 --> 00:18:34,567
Well, I'm not salivating
just yet.

284
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:36,900
I think it's a lazy idea.

285
00:18:36,967 --> 00:18:38,100
I'm sorry.

286
00:18:38,167 --> 00:18:39,900
What do you mean?

287
00:18:39,967 --> 00:18:41,133
Well basically you're telling us

288
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:44,133
that your groundbreaking selling
point is for us to tie-up

289
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:47,467
with a huge ice cream company
and put our pili nuts into that.

290
00:18:47,533 --> 00:18:48,633
I see it's a lazy idea

291
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:51,467
because I wish you could've
sprinkled it more

292
00:18:51,533 --> 00:18:52,933
with your creativity.

293
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,467
Yes of course for sure

294
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:56,867
it's going to be such
a huge hit, you know.

295
00:18:56,967 --> 00:18:58,767
But after the hype what's going
to happen then?

296
00:18:58,833 --> 00:19:01,000
In the process, we're not
going to develop

297
00:19:01,067 --> 00:19:03,200
any loyal consumers
that will be inclined

298
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:05,233
to have pili nuts
in their lives.

299
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:08,000
At the end of the day,
it's about ice cream,

300
00:19:08,067 --> 00:19:09,433
not pili nuts.

301
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:11,133
That's the star of the show,
right?

302
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:32,067
I don't mean to be harsh
or anything.

303
00:19:32,133 --> 00:19:33,400
I just...

304
00:19:33,467 --> 00:19:35,933
I just don't think
it's working out.

305
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,033
I think you should go back
to the drawing board

306
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:40,000
and start from zero.

307
00:19:40,067 --> 00:19:42,200
You studied in America, right?

308
00:19:42,267 --> 00:19:44,200
You're an Ivy Leaguer.

309
00:19:44,267 --> 00:19:46,367
That's wonderful.

310
00:19:46,433 --> 00:19:48,500
I'm just a bit shocked
and appalled

311
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:51,300
that's what they taught you
in school.

312
00:19:51,367 --> 00:19:55,800
It kinda makes me sad
because if that's how they are

313
00:19:55,867 --> 00:19:58,433
I wonder how America
will be great again.

314
00:19:58,500 --> 00:20:01,833
- Celeste?
- No, I mean no harm.

315
00:20:01,933 --> 00:20:05,233
I was just being factual.

316
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:06,500
It's just the truth.

317
00:20:43,533 --> 00:20:45,900
What are we doing here?

318
00:20:45,967 --> 00:20:47,500
This is what will help you.

319
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:52,200
Grandma!

320
00:20:52,267 --> 00:20:53,700
Grandma!

321
00:20:53,767 --> 00:20:55,067
Wait a second.

322
00:20:55,133 --> 00:20:56,567
- Hi, Grandma.
- Basti.

323
00:20:56,633 --> 00:20:59,700
What do you want?

324
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:00,833
Just a second...

325
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:06,467
She is the grandmother
respected by all.

326
00:21:06,533 --> 00:21:07,667
If you get her trust

327
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:09,967
you can get the trust
of the whole community.

328
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,167
Grandma...

329
00:21:17,733 --> 00:21:20,067
I want you to meet
my girlfriend.

330
00:21:20,133 --> 00:21:22,300
This is Tiffany.

331
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:24,867
Hi.

332
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:28,067
It's my pleasure to meet you.

333
00:21:28,133 --> 00:21:32,867
What can I do for you,
my child, Basti?

334
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:36,100
We're hoping that you
will help us convince

335
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:39,233
the people here
to join my project.

336
00:21:41,033 --> 00:21:42,333
Is that so?

337
00:21:42,433 --> 00:21:43,967
In exchange for what?

338
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:59,533
Well, how about targeting
the Filipino communities abroad?

339
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:03,100
I don't think the new generation
of Filipinos will like it.

340
00:22:03,167 --> 00:22:05,000
Creating it
as a food supplement?

341
00:22:05,067 --> 00:22:07,133
Bad idea, bad!

342
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:11,900
Using pili in powdered form.

343
00:22:11,967 --> 00:22:14,700
Do you have other
workable ideas?

344
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:27,200
Celeste, can we talk?

345
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:05,200
I thought Grandma will help us
to convince the people here

346
00:23:05,267 --> 00:23:06,800
to join my project?

347
00:23:06,867 --> 00:23:09,367
Do you regret that it seems
all your efforts

348
00:23:09,433 --> 00:23:10,967
and services didn't go anywhere?

349
00:23:11,033 --> 00:23:13,567
Now I know why you and Mikoy
didn't last long.

350
00:23:13,633 --> 00:23:16,567
What you call standards
is merely to hide

351
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:19,100
that you are a sad, little girl.

352
00:23:19,167 --> 00:23:21,133
Honestly, do you think
I'm scared of you?

353
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:23,133
Scared? No.

354
00:23:23,233 --> 00:23:25,833
Envious? Yes.

355
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:27,467
You've really perfected this.

356
00:23:27,533 --> 00:23:29,300
And that's one thing
that impresses me.

357
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:31,433
If there's one thing
that you want to learn

358
00:23:31,500 --> 00:23:33,467
you become really,
really good at it.

359
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:43,267
I'm sure you will come back
to me.

360
00:23:43,333 --> 00:23:46,033
Not a good fit for Celeste.

361
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:48,267
I'm the only one
who understands you.

362
00:23:53,367 --> 00:23:56,100
Whoever is at fault between us
that's not important anymore.

363
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:58,833
Tell me that now.

364
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:01,467
You said that it was my fault
and now I should forget it.

365
00:24:01,533 --> 00:24:02,933
It's you who left.
